{:metadata {:description [{"text" "<p>Amino acid permeases are integral membrane proteins involved in the transport of amino acids into the cell. A number of such proteins have been found to be evolutionary related [[cite:PUB00003402], [cite:PUB00001779], [cite:PUB00005006]]. These proteins seem to contain up to 12 transmembrane segments. The best conserved region in this family is located in the second transmembrane segment.</p>\n\n<p>This family is specific for the fungal amino acid permeases including the general amino acid permease AGP1, which perferentially transports Asp and Glu but can transport other amino acids [[cite:PUB00085165]]; GAP1, which transports Leu and Phe, and GAP3 which transports Phe [[cite:PUB00085166]].</p>", "llm" false, "checked" false, "updated" false}], :is-reviewed-llm false, :representative-structure nil, :overlaps-with nil, :member-databases {"ncbifam" {"TIGR00913" "amino acid permease"}}, :is-updated-llm false, :name {"name" "Amino acid permease, fungi", "short" "Amino_acid_permease_fungi"}, :wikipedia nil, :source-database "interpro", :type "family", :counters {"structures" 0, "domain_architectures" 0, "proteomes" 840, "taxa" 2293, "subfamilies" 0, "interactions" 0, "matches" 3888, "sets" 0, "proteins" 3883, "structural_models" {"alphafold" 2657}, "pathways" 0}, :integrated nil, :cross-references {}, :set-info nil, :accession "IPR004762", :literature {"PUB00003402" {"URL" nil, "issue" "4", "authors" ["Weber E" "Chevallier MR" "Jund R."], "ISO_journal" "J. Mol. Evol.", "DOI_URL" "http://dx.doi.org/10.1007/BF02101197", "medline_journal" "J Mol Evol", "title" "Evolutionary relationship and secondary structure predictions in four transport proteins of Saccharomyces cerevisiae.", "year" 1988, "raw_pages" "341-50", "volume" "27", "ISBN" nil, "PMID" 3146645}, "PUB00001779" {"URL" nil, "issue" "1", "authors" ["Vandenbol M" "Jauniaux JC" "Grenson M."], "ISO_journal" "Gene", "DOI_URL" "http://dx.doi.org/10.1016/0378-1119(89)90413-7", "medline